Market players in the smart inhaler technology sector are focusing on research and development activities to introduce next-generation inhaler devices with enhanced functionalities and connectivity options. Companies like Adherium, Amiko Digital Health, and GlaxoSmithKline plc are investing in smart inhaler technology to cater to the evolving needs of patients and healthcare providers. By leveraging data analytics and digital health platforms, smart inhaler devices enable personalized treatment plans, inhaler technique improvement, and early detection of worsening symptoms, thereby improving patient engagement and overall health outcomes.

